notes_ui.feature
@ui @notes
Feature: Notes Management

  Background:
    Given an authenticated user exists

  @smoke @positive
  Scenario: User creates a new note successfully
    When the user creates a note with title "Shopping List" and description "Buy milk"
    Then the note should be created successfully
    And the note should be available in the user's notes list

  @positive
  Scenario: User deletes an existing note
    Given the user has a note with title "Temporary Note" and description "Delete me"
    When the user deletes the note
    Then the note should be deleted successfully
    But the note should not be available in the user's notes list

  @negative @validation
  Scenario Outline: Note creation is rejected when required information is missing
    When the user tries to create a note with title "<title>" and description "<description>"
    Then the note creation should be rejected
    And the error message should mention "<missing_field>"

    Examples:
      | title         | description | missing_field |
      |               | Buy milk    | title         |
      | Shopping List |             | description   |


